com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class DefaultToStringMessageTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.DefaultToStringMessageTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFromMessageTransformer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ToStringMessageTransformer

    public class DefaultToStringMessageTransformer
extends Object
implements IFromMessageTransformer
    Converts an IFIXMessage to a number of different String representations suitable for display.

    The different String formats correspond to the standard format values defined in IFIXMessage.toString(int).

    This is the default message transformer used by IFIXMessage.toString() methods of IFIXMessage objects which use FIXMessageFormatter to supply their FIX specific functionality.

        The other way to create this transformer is with the null constructor and then set the format by means of setAttributes.

        delimiter - delimiter character to use when converting to full string, usually SOH ("")
